---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  titulo="How We Work — LRA Engineering Methodology"
  descripcion="The 6-phase engineering process, standards, and principles behind every LRA Cloud Operations engagement. GitOps, IaC-first, security by default, observability before go-live."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden" style="background-color: #0A2540;">
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-40"
      style="background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(147,184,255,0.15) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 28px 28px;"
    >
    </div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 sm:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span
          class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-full mb-6"
          style="background: rgba(30,111,255,0.15); color: #93b8ff; border: 1px solid rgba(30,111,255,0.3);"
        >
          Engineering Methodology
        </span>
        <h1
          class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white mb-5"
          style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          How we work
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg max-w-2xl" style="color: rgba(147,184,255,0.8);">
          Every engagement follows the same process: assess, design, build,
          validate, document, operate. The same principles apply whether the
          project is a Terraform module or a production EKS cluster.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PHASE 1–6 -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-14">
        <p
          class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3"
          style="color: #1E6FFF;"
        >
          The process
        </p>
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-extrabold"
          style="color: #0A2540; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          6-phase engagement model
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base mt-3 max-w-xl mx-auto" style="color: #64748b;">
          Each phase has defined entry criteria, deliverables, and exit
          criteria. Nothing is skipped. Phases 1–3 are sequential; 4–6 are
          continuous.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        {
          [
            {
              phase: '01',
              name: 'Discovery & Assessment',
              duration: '1–2 weeks',
              color: '#7C3AED',
              bg: 'rgba(124,58,237,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(124,58,237,0.15)',
              what: 'Understand the current infrastructure, identify gaps, define success criteria. No assumptions.',
              deliverables: [
                'Current architecture diagram',
                'Gap analysis vs. target state',
                'Risk register',
                'Project scope document',
              ],
            },
            {
              phase: '02',
              name: 'Architecture Design',
              duration: '1–2 weeks',
              color: '#0284C7',
              bg: 'rgba(2,132,199,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(2,132,199,0.15)',
              what: 'Design the target architecture with explicit trade-off documentation. Every decision is justified, not assumed.',
              deliverables: [
                'Target architecture diagrams',
                'Infrastructure module design',
                'Security model (IAM, network, secrets)',
                'Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)',
              ],
            },
            {
              phase: '03',
              name: 'Implementation',
              duration: '2–8 weeks',
              color: '#1E6FFF',
              bg: 'rgba(30,111,255,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(30,111,255,0.15)',
              what: 'Build the infrastructure using IaC-first principles. Every resource is in Terraform. Every application deployment is GitOps.',
              deliverables: [
                'Terraform modules (per component)',
                'CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions + Jenkins)',
                'Kubernetes manifests with GitOps delivery',
                'Runbooks for operational procedures',
              ],
            },
            {
              phase: '04',
              name: 'Validation & Testing',
              duration: 'Continuous',
              color: '#047857',
              bg: 'rgba(4,120,87,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(4,120,87,0.15)',
              what: 'Every implementation is tested against the requirements defined in Phase 1. No deployment without a passing pipeline.',
              deliverables: [
                'Automated test suite (pytest, ShellCheck)',
                'SonarCloud quality gate results',
                'Load test results for critical paths',
                'Security scan reports',
              ],
            },
            {
              phase: '05',
              name: 'Documentation',
              duration: 'Continuous',
              color: '#B45309',
              bg: 'rgba(180,83,9,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(180,83,9,0.15)',
              what: 'Documentation is written alongside code, not after. Architecture decisions, runbooks, and operational guides are deliverables, not afterthoughts.',
              deliverables: [
                'README per module with input/output documentation',
                'Runbooks for each operational scenario',
                'Architecture Decision Records',
                'On-call guide with escalation paths',
              ],
            },
            {
              phase: '06',
              name: 'Operations & Handoff',
              duration: 'Ongoing',
              color: '#BE123C',
              bg: 'rgba(190,18,60,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(190,18,60,0.15)',
              what: 'Production readiness review, observability validation, team enablement. The engagement ends when the client team can operate independently.',
              deliverables: [
                'Production readiness checklist (47 points)',
                'Observability dashboards (Grafana)',
                'Alerting configured and tested',
                'Team knowledge transfer sessions',
              ],
            },
          ].map(
            ({
              phase,
              name,
              duration,
              color,
              bg,
              border,
              what,
              deliverables,
            }) => (
              <div
                class="rounded-2xl p-7"
                style={`background: ${bg}; border: 1px solid ${border};`}
              >
                <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start gap-5">
                  <div
                    class="flex-shrink-0 w-14 h-14 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center font-extrabold text-lg"
                    style={`background: ${color}; color: white;`}
                  >
                    {phase}
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-2">
                      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold" style="color: #0A2540;">
                        {name}
                      </h3>
                      <span
                        class="text-xs font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full"
                        style={`background: ${bg}; color: ${color}; border: 1px solid ${border};`}
                      >
                        {duration}
                      </span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm mb-4" style="color: #64748b;">
                      {what}
                    </p>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                      {deliverables.map((d) => (
                        <span
                          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full"
                          style={`background: white; color: ${color}; border: 1px solid ${border};`}
                        >
                          <svg
                            class="w-3 h-3"
                            fill="none"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            aria-hidden="true"
                          >
                            <path
                              stroke-linecap="round"
                              stroke-linejoin="round"
                              stroke-width="2"
                              d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"
                            />
                          </svg>
                          {d}
                        </span>
                      ))}
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            )
          )
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ENGINEERING STANDARDS -->
  <section
    style="background: #F8FAFC; border-top: 1px solid #E2E8F0;"
    class="py-20"
  >
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-14">
        <p
          class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3"
          style="color: #1E6FFF;"
        >
          Non-negotiables
        </p>
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-extrabold"
          style="color: #0A2540; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          Engineering standards
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base mt-3 max-w-xl mx-auto" style="color: #64748b;">
          These are not preferences. They are the minimum bar for every
          deliverable.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        {
          [
            {
              title: 'IaC-first',
              icon: 'M10 20l4-16m4 4l4 4-4 4M6 16l-4-4 4-4',
              points: [
                'Every AWS resource in a Terraform module',
                'No ClickOps in production, ever',
                'S3 remote state + DynamoDB lock on all projects',
                'terraform plan required before every apply',
              ],
            },
            {
              title: 'Semantic commits & Git hygiene',
              icon: 'M9 17v-2m3 2v-4m3 4v-6m2 10H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z',
              points: [
                'Conventional commits: feat/fix/ci/docs/chore',
                'Protected main branch — PRs required',
                'CI must pass before merge',
                'No force-push to main',
              ],
            },
            {
              title: 'set -euo pipefail in all shell scripts',
              icon: 'M8 9l3 3-3 3m5 0h3M5 20h14a2 2 0 002-2V6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z',
              points: [
                '-e: exit on any error',
                '-u: treat unset variables as errors',
                '-o pipefail: catch pipeline failures',
                'ShellCheck CI validation on all .sh files',
              ],
            },
            {
              title: 'Zero static credentials',
              icon: 'M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z',
              points: [
                'GitHub Actions uses OIDC federation',
                'EC2/EKS uses IAM roles (IRSA)',
                'SSM Session Manager replaces SSH',
                'No AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID in any secret store',
              ],
            },
          ].map(({ title, icon, points }) => (
            <div
              class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-7"
              style="border: 1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.06); box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(15,23,42,0.04);"
            >
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
                <div
                  class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center"
                  style="background: #EEF4FF;"
                >
                  <svg
                    class="w-5 h-5"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    style="color: #1E6FFF;"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="1.5"
                      d={icon}
                    />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-bold" style="color: #0A2540;">
                  {title}
                </h3>
              </div>
              <ul class="space-y-2.5">
                {points.map((p) => (
                  <li
                    class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-sm"
                    style="color: #64748b;"
                  >
                    <svg
                      class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                      fill="none"
                      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                      stroke="currentColor"
                      style="color: #1E6FFF;"
                      aria-hidden="true"
                    >
                      <path
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"
                      />
                    </svg>
                    {p}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GITOPS PRINCIPLES -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20 border-t border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <p
            class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3"
            style="color: #1E6FFF;"
          >
            GitOps principles
          </p>
          <h2
            class="text-3xl font-extrabold mb-5"
            style="color: #0A2540; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
          >
            Git is the source of truth. Always.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-base mb-6" style="color: #64748b;">
            GitOps means the desired state of the system is declared in Git, and
            a controller continuously reconciles the actual state against it.
            Not as a best practice — as a technical guarantee.
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            {
              [
                {
                  title: 'No manual kubectl apply in production',
                  desc: 'ArgoCD is the only mechanism for applying changes to a managed cluster. selfHeal=true enforces this.',
                },
                {
                  title: 'Every infrastructure change is a commit',
                  desc: 'terraform apply runs from CI only. Local applies are blocked on production backends.',
                },
                {
                  title: 'Prune enabled on all ArgoCD applications',
                  desc: 'Removing a manifest from Git removes the resource from the cluster. Git defines complete state.',
                },
                {
                  title: 'Drift is an incident',
                  desc: 'Any difference between Git and the cluster triggers an alert. ArgoCD Degraded state is paged, not ignored.',
                },
              ].map(({ title, desc }) => (
                <li class="flex gap-3">
                  <div
                    class="w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full mt-1.5"
                    style="background: #1E6FFF; height: 1.25rem;"
                  />
                  <div>
                    <p
                      class="text-sm font-semibold mb-0.5"
                      style="color: #0A2540;"
                    >
                      {title}
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-sm" style="color: #64748b;">
                      {desc}
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </li>
              ))
            }
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="rounded-2xl p-7 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed"
          style="background: #0A2540; color: #94a3b8;"
        >
          <p
            class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-4"
            style="color: rgba(147,184,255,0.6);"
          >
            GitOps delivery pipeline
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            {
              [
                {
                  step: '1',
                  label: 'git push (feature branch)',
                  color: '#60A5FA',
                },
                {
                  step: '↓',
                  label: 'Pull request + code review',
                  color: '#94a3b8',
                },
                {
                  step: '2',
                  label: 'CI: terraform plan + tests + docker build',
                  color: '#34D399',
                },
                { step: '↓', label: 'Merge to main', color: '#94a3b8' },
                {
                  step: '3',
                  label: 'Jenkins: build artifact + push ECR',
                  color: '#F59E0B',
                },
                {
                  step: '↓',
                  label: 'Update image tag in k8s manifest',
                  color: '#94a3b8',
                },
                {
                  step: '4',
                  label: 'ArgoCD detects diff (≤ 3 min)',
                  color: '#A78BFA',
                },
                {
                  step: '↓',
                  label: 'kubectl apply (by ArgoCD only)',
                  color: '#94a3b8',
                },
                {
                  step: '✓',
                  label: 'Cluster reflects Git state',
                  color: '#34D399',
                },
              ].map(({ step, label, color }) => (
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <span
                    class="w-6 text-center text-xs font-bold flex-shrink-0"
                    style={`color: ${color};`}
                  >
                    {step}
                  </span>
                  <span style={`color: ${color};`}>{label}</span>
                </div>
              ))
            }
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECURITY BY DEFAULT -->
  <section
    style="background: #F8FAFC; border-top: 1px solid #E2E8F0;"
    class="py-20"
  >
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <p
          class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3"
          style="color: #1E6FFF;"
        >
          Security by default
        </p>
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-extrabold"
          style="color: #0A2540; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          Security is built in, not bolted on
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        {
          [
            {
              label: 'Identity',
              items: [
                'OIDC federation for CI/CD',
                'IAM roles with least-privilege',
                'IRSA for Kubernetes workloads',
                'MFA on all human accounts',
              ],
            },
            {
              label: 'Network',
              items: [
                'Compute in private subnets',
                'No port 22 in security groups',
                'SSM replaces SSH everywhere',
                'VPC endpoints to reduce blast radius',
              ],
            },
            {
              label: 'Secrets',
              items: [
                'AWS Secrets Manager for runtime secrets',
                'No secrets in environment variables',
                'No secrets in code or Git history',
                'Rotation policies on all credentials',
              ],
            },
          ].map(({ label, items }) => (
            <div
              class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6"
              style="border: 1px solid #E2E8F0;"
            >
              <h3
                class="text-sm font-bold mb-4 pb-3 border-b border-gray-100"
                style="color: #0A2540;"
              >
                {label}
              </h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2.5">
                {items.map((item) => (
                  <li
                    class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm"
                    style="color: #64748b;"
                  >
                    <svg
                      class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                      fill="none"
                      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                      stroke="currentColor"
                      style="color: #1E6FFF;"
                      aria-hidden="true"
                    >
                      <path
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"
                      />
                    </svg>
                    {item}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OBSERVABILITY FIRST -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20 border-t border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <p
            class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3"
            style="color: #1E6FFF;"
          >
            Observability first
          </p>
          <h2
            class="text-3xl font-extrabold mb-4"
            style="color: #0A2540; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
          >
            Prometheus + Grafana before go-live
          </h2>
          <p class="text-base mb-6" style="color: #64748b;">
            No production deployment goes live without observability configured,
            dashboards built, and alerts tested. Observability is a gate, not an
            afterthought.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            {
              [
                'Prometheus metrics collection on all workloads',
                'Grafana dashboards for cluster + application RED metrics',
                'Alertmanager routes P1/P2 to on-call, P3/P4 to ticket',
                'CloudWatch for AWS-level metrics and CloudTrail audit',
                'Structured JSON logging from all services',
                'Alert testing: chaos drill before go-live',
              ].map((item) => (
                <div
                  class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm"
                  style="color: #64748b;"
                >
                  <div
                    class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full flex-shrink-0"
                    style="background: #1E6FFF;"
                  />
                  {item}
                </div>
              ))
            }
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {
            [
              {
                metric: 'RED',
                label: 'Rate · Errors · Duration',
                desc: 'Per-service metrics tracked from day one',
              },
              {
                metric: 'USE',
                label: 'Utilization · Saturation · Errors',
                desc: 'Infrastructure metrics for every resource',
              },
              {
                metric: '< 3m',
                label: 'Alert response time',
                desc: 'ArgoCD + Alertmanager default polling',
              },
              {
                metric: '47',
                label: 'Production readiness checks',
                desc: 'Every engagement validated before go-live',
              },
            ].map(({ metric, label, desc }) => (
              <div
                class="rounded-2xl p-5 text-center"
                style="background: #EEF4FF; border: 1px solid #c3d9ff;"
              >
                <div
                  class="text-2xl font-extrabold mb-1"
                  style="color: #1E6FFF; letter-spacing: -0.04em;"
                >
                  {metric}
                </div>
                <div class="text-xs font-bold mb-1" style="color: #0A2540;">
                  {label}
                </div>
                <div class="text-xs" style="color: #64748b;">
                  {desc}
                </div>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RED HAT STANDARDS -->
  <section style="background: #0A2540;" class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <p
          class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3"
          style="color: rgba(147,184,255,0.6);"
        >
          Red Hat engineering standards
        </p>
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white"
          style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          Battle-tested open source practices
        </h2>
        <p
          class="text-base mt-3 max-w-xl mx-auto"
          style="color: rgba(147,184,255,0.75);"
        >
          The k8s-on-premise project applies Red Hat engineering practices to
          bare-metal Kubernetes. These same standards govern all lra-cloud-ops
          projects.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        {
          [
            {
              title: 'Idempotent provisioning',
              desc: 'Every script can run twice and produce the same result. set -euo pipefail. Check before act.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Documentation in code',
              desc: 'No separate docs directory. README files live next to the code they document.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Everything auditable',
              desc: 'CloudTrail for AWS, ArgoCD history for K8s, git log for code. No change without a record.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Minimal dependencies',
              desc: 'Use the standard library. Use the managed service. Add a dependency only when there is no alternative.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Explicit over implicit',
              desc: 'All Terraform resources are explicit. No default values that hide security settings. No magic.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Automation over runbooks',
              desc: 'If a runbook step can be automated, automate it. Runbooks are for decisions, not commands.',
            },
          ].map(({ title, desc }) => (
            <div
              class="rounded-xl p-5"
              style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);"
            >
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2 text-white">{title}</h3>
              <p class="text-sm" style="color: rgba(147,184,255,0.7);">
                {desc}
              </p>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20 border-t border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl font-extrabold mb-4"
        style="color: #0A2540; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
      >
        See the methodology in practice
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base mb-10" style="color: #64748b;">
        Every project in the portfolio is built using this process. Review the
        case studies or schedule a conversation to discuss how it applies to
        your infrastructure.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a
          href="/projects"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-8 py-3.5 rounded-xl font-semibold text-white transition-all hover:-translate-y-px"
